			<p>It&#8217;s not just technology.  I was a physician spending about half of my time on administration of a hospital department.  The hospital administrators would come in with ideas, naturally involving physicians on the medical staff.  When I tried to discuss the likely reactions of the physicians, I saw the same look of contempt on the administrators&#8217; faces.  &#8220;We don&#8217;t have to think about, or deal with, those jerks, that&#8217;s just your job.  Just get them on board so our great ideas will work.&#8221;  You cannot overestimate the contempt that managers have for those who can actually do the work.</p>
