			<p>Mr. Shirky&#8217;s comment about the importance of understanding the tradeoff between features, quality, and time rings a bell. I&#8217;ve always formulated it like this:</p>
<p>Fast. Accurate. Complete. At best, pick two.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s the dream that you can get all three that will trip you up. If you can&#8217;t understand that the third element always undercuts the other two, then you&#8217;re doomed to disappointment.</p>
